<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2774] Java final fields may be changed by Groovy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2774</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1875&quot; title=&quot;private fields and private methods are not private&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-1875&quot;&gt;GROOVY-1875&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def s = &apos;12&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
s.value = &apos;ABCD&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
println s&lt;br/&gt;
==&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
AB&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &apos;value&apos; field is a private final variable in class java.lang.String.&lt;br/&gt;
Therfore Groovy makes String mutable!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12814199">GROOVY-2774</key>
